item.title: Cant compile any 718 client help please
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

This belongs in client help, but anyways…

This is 14 warnings and 3 errors. Errors are something bad, warnings usually are not.

src\Class466.java:11: error: cannot find symbol
                        JSObject.getWindow(applet).eval(string);
                                ^
  symbol:   method getWindow(Applet)
  location: class JSObject
src\Class466.java:19: error: cannot find symbol
                        return JSObject.getWindow(applet).call(string, null);
                                       ^
  symbol:   method getWindow(Applet)
  location: class JSObject
src\Class466.java:27: error: cannot find symbol
                        return JSObject.getWindow(applet).call(string, objects);

Those are your three errors, with those fixed, everything else will work fine. Can you post your Class466. Or if it’s a large file, just post your imports.

Do you have the correct dependencies for JSObject? (Do you have jfxrt.jar)

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/23241600/compilation-error-in-maven-java8-build-cannot-find-symbol-jsobject-getwindow

That may help you out.
